```
1. Open the text file and read it line by line:
```c++
std::ifstream file("example.txt"); // Replace with your file path
```
1. Create a function to tokenize the lines:
```c++
std::vector<std::string> tokenize(std::string line) {
    std::vector<std::string> tokens;
    std::string token;

    std::stringstream ss(line);
    while (getline(ss, token,'')) {
        tokens.push_back(token);
    }
    return tokens;
}
```
1. Check for the occurrence of the specific word and count it:
```c++
int countWord(std::vector<std::string> tokens) {
    int count = 0;
    for (std::string token : tokens) {
        if (token == wordToCount) {
            count++;
        }
    }
    return count;
}
```
1. Read the file line by line and call the countWord function:
